    <div id="c1" class="bz_comment">

      <div class="bz_comment_head">
        <div class="bz_comment_user">
          <span class="vcard"><span class="fn">Tab Atkins</span>
</span>
          
          
          <span class="bz_comment_user_images">
          </span>

        </div>


        <div class="bz_comment_meta">
          <a href="show_bug.cgi?id=29084#c1">Comment 1</a>
          <span class="bz_comment_time torelativedatetime" data-ts="2011-10-19 20:52:52">2011-10-19 20:52:52 PDT</span>
          
        </div>

      </div>




<div class="bz_comment_text">'10%' is the correct computed value - percentages are resolved at &quot;used value&quot; time.  However, the getComputedStyle function is a bit of a misnomer, and actually returns a mix of computed and used values.

Which properties return what is underdefined right now.  Ideally we should wait for the CSSOM spec to define this, but in the absence of that, we can look at what other browsers do.

In particular, Firefox returns used values for these properties.  I think that's useful, and we should probably match them.</div>
    </div>
    


    <div id="c2" class="bz_comment">

      <div class="bz_comment_head">
        <div class="bz_comment_user">
          <span class="vcard"><span class="fn">Mike Sherov</span>
</span>
          
          
          <span class="bz_comment_user_images">
          </span>

        </div>


        <div class="bz_comment_meta">
          <a href="show_bug.cgi?id=29084#c2">Comment 2</a>
          <span class="bz_comment_time torelativedatetime" data-ts="2011-11-21 14:59:27">2011-11-21 14:59:27 PST</span>
          
        </div>

      </div>




<div class="bz_comment_text"><span class="quote">&gt; In particular, Firefox returns used values for these properties.</span >

Yes, FF, IE9, and Opera all use the &quot;used value&quot; instead of the &quot;computed value&quot;.  

<span class="quote">&gt; I think that's useful, and we should probably match them.</span >

Yes, it's immensely useful, and in particular, several popular javascript libraries have bugs open for it:
 * <a rel="nofollow" href="http://bugs.jquery.com/ticket/10639">http://bugs.jquery.com/ticket/10639</a>
 * <a rel="nofollow" href="http://yuilibrary.com/projects/yui3/ticket/2529799">http://yuilibrary.com/projects/yui3/ticket/2529799</a></div>
    </div>
    


    <div id="c3" class="bz_comment">

      <div class="bz_comment_head">
        <div class="bz_comment_user">
          <span class="vcard"><span class="fn">Ryosuke Niwa</span>
</span>
          
          
          <span class="bz_comment_user_images">
          </span>

        </div>


        <div class="bz_comment_meta">
          <a href="show_bug.cgi?id=29084#c3">Comment 3</a>
          <span class="bz_comment_time torelativedatetime" data-ts="2011-11-21 15:48:08">2011-11-21 15:48:08 PST</span>
          
        </div>

      </div>




<div class="bz_comment_text">What does Trident do?</div>
    </div>
    


    <div id="c4" class="bz_comment">

      <div class="bz_comment_head">
        <div class="bz_comment_user">
          <span class="vcard"><span class="fn">Tab Atkins</span>
</span>
          
          
          <span class="bz_comment_user_images">
          </span>

