          <span class="bz_comment_time torelativedatetime" data-ts="2011-11-21 19:11:35">2011-11-21 19:11:35 PST</span>
          
        </div>

      </div>




<div class="bz_comment_text">That makes sense. If it's display none or disconnected, pixel values (used values) aren't possible nor easy to correctly resolve, and so therefore should report computed values (cascaded values or whatever you want to call it).</div>
    </div>
    


    <div id="c11" class="bz_comment">

      <div class="bz_comment_head">
        <div class="bz_comment_user">
