<div class="bz_comment_text">(In reply to <a href="show_bug.cgi?id=29084#c10">comment #10</a>)
<span class="quote">&gt; That makes sense. If it's display none or disconnected, pixel values (used values) aren't possible nor easy to correctly resolve, and so therefore should report computed values (cascaded values or whatever you want to call it).</span >

Sorry I made a mistake that thought the list of properties that getComputedStyle() may return the used value included left/right/top/bottom. Actually the draft (<a rel="nofollow" href="http://dev.w3.org/csswg/cssom/#resolved-value">http://dev.w3.org/csswg/cssom/#resolved-value</a>) implies for left/right/top/bottom getComputedStyle() should return the computed style.</div>
    </div>
    


    <div id="c12" class="bz_comment">

      <div class="bz_comment_head">
        <div class="bz_comment_user">
