          <span class="bz_comment_time torelativedatetime" data-ts="2011-11-21 20:07:00">2011-11-21 20:07:00 PST</span>
          
        </div>

      </div>




<div class="bz_comment_text">I'm sorry for causing any confusion. This is perhaps the correct behavior, but then this exposes the fact that although top/left/right/bottom follow the draft spec, margin*, padding*, border* do not and FF, IE9, and Opera do follow the spec for margin*, padding*, and border*.  

Can we at least then bring those properties in line with the other browsers, as it would also match the draft?

Shall I create another ticket for those properties separately?</div>
    </div>
    


