<div class="bz_comment_text">Just to be complete here, this fiddle shows it all:

<a rel="nofollow" href="http://jsfiddle.net/u4F8m/5/embedded/result/">http://jsfiddle.net/u4F8m/5/embedded/result/</a>

IE9, O, FF all have &quot;used values&quot; for the properties listed.

Webkit has &quot;computed values&quot; for margin-*,top/left/right/bottom

margin-* is clearly a bug, as it neither matches the other browsers nor the spec.

top/left/right/bottom match the spec, and not the other browsers, and I believe the spec should be amended.</div>
    </div>
    


